Pretoria - Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (CoGTA) Minister Des van Rooyen has payed tribute to the late Deputy Mayor of Richmond Municipality in KwaZulu-Natal, Thandazile Phoswa.Phoswa was reportedly murdered on Sunday.The Minister has conveyed his heartfelt condolences to her family and colleagues. It is the passing of such committed servants of our people that leaves us poorer in our determination to deliver services to the people. We hope that her passing will motivate all of us to keep her legacy alive by ensuring that we deliver to our communities as expected, said Minister Van Rooyen.A few weeks ago, the Municipal Manager of the same municipality, S'bu Sithole, was assassinated.The department called on bereaved colleagues to draw motivation to work hard, do more and continue the good work that their late colleagues had started in the municipality. We urge communities to work with law enforcement agencies to bring all these cases to finality, said the department. - SAnews.gov.zaPretoria - The Inter-Ministerial Committee (IMC) on Vuwani has welcomed the plans put in place to assist matriculants with preparations for their final year examinations, says the Ministry of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (COGTA).Pretoria The South African Local Government Association (SALGA) has welcomed the Budget Vote delivered by CoGTA Minister Des van Rooyen, saying it is encouraged by the upward positive trend of service delivery which restores human dignity.Midrand - President Jacob Zuma says great strides have been made in delivering basic services to South African communities in the past 14 years since the inception of a democratic local government.